---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="What DonateCrate Accepts"
  description="See which clothing, shoes, and household textiles DonateCrate accepts for monthly pickup."
>
  <main class="simple-page">
    <a class="back-link" href="/">Back to home</a>
    <span class="eyebrow">Accepted Items</span>
    <h1>Clothing, shoes, and household linens that are clean, dry, and ready to bag.</h1>
    <p class="simple-page__lede">
      The easiest pickups happen when items are simple to sort and easy to carry. If it is a clean textile your
      household is ready to part with, it is usually a good fit.
    </p>
    <div class="simple-grid">
      <article>
        <h2>Clothing</h2>
        <p>T-shirts, denim, jackets, dresses, kids clothing, and seasonal apparel that are clean and dry.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Shoes</h2>
        <p>Paired footwear in reusable condition. Keep pairs together so the pickup stays easy to sort.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Linens</h2>
        <p>Sheets, towels, blankets, and comparable home textiles that are dry, contained, and ready to bag.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
    <section class="feature-band">
      <article>
        <span class="eyebrow">Best results</span>
        <h2>Bag items the way you would want to receive them.</h2>
        <p>Keep everything clean, dry, and contained so pickup day feels smooth and the items are ready for reuse.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span class="eyebrow">Not sure?</span>
        <h2>When in doubt, keep it textile-focused.</h2>
        <p>DonateCrate is designed around clothing, shoes, and linens rather than bulky household goods or mixed-item junk loads.</p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
